    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 240\u00baC/ 220\u00baC (fan)/ gas 9</p><p>Put a large <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottom[s] from going soggy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>dried yeast</strong> to a large bowl with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>warm water </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give it a good mix up and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mushroom-pizza-with-homemade-stracciatella/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s] </strong>finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> tomato paste</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and stir it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato base</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mushroom-pizza-with-homemade-stracciatella/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> pizza base mix </strong>to the bowl with the yeast</p><p>Gradually add up to 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[115ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml] </span><strong>warm water </strong>(you may not need all of it), a little at a time, and gently mix with a plastic spatula until a sticky dough ball has formed</p><p>Tip the dough out onto a floured work surface and cut into 1 per person</p><p>Toss each dough ball in a light dusting of <strong>flour </strong>until coated, rounding the ball as you go (no need to knead!)</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mushroom-pizza-with-homemade-stracciatella/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Press each <strong>dough ball</strong> in the centre and gently push outwards, with your fingertips, leaving the rim of the pizza untouched to form a crust (don't worry if the dough rips, just stick it back together and carry on!)</p><p>Tip: Dust with extra sprinkles of flour as you go to stop it sticking!</p><p>Keep going until your base[s] is slightly larger than a side plate \u2013 this is your <strong>pizza base[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mushroom-pizza-with-homemade-stracciatella/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>pizza base[s]</strong> to the heated baking tray[s]</p><p>Spread the <strong>tomato base</strong> evenly over your pizza base[s] with the back of a spoon</p><p>Top with your <strong>sliced mushroom </strong>and <strong>sliced shallot</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 12-15 min or until or until the pizza bases are golden and crisp \u2013 this is your <strong>mushroom pizza[s]</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Do this in batches!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mushroom-pizza-with-homemade-stracciatella/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into small pieces and add them to a medium bowl with your <strong>soft cheese</strong>, 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>milk</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give it a good stir \u2013 this is your <strong>homemade stracciatella</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mushroom-pizza-with-homemade-stracciatella/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Chop your <strong>basil </strong>roughly</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-mushroom-pizza-with-homemade-stracciatella/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To assemble, drizzle your <strong>truffle oil </strong>over the <strong>mushroom pizza </strong>then top with the <strong>homemade stracciatella</strong>, a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong>, the <strong>chopped basil </strong>and your <strong>salad </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>truffled mushroom pizza with homemade stracciatella</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
